    "narrative": "For Ghost Ride the WHIP, the priority today is capitalizing on favorable matchups against high-xERA arms, with **Corbin Carroll** standing out as the clear must-start of the day. Boasting an 87.14 score, **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a strong matchup against Davis Martin (4.68 xERA) and an ideal spot in the two-hole, bolstered by a 0.372 xwOBA that signals positive regression. **Mickey Moniak** (75.75) and **James Wood** (66.49) follow closely as high-ceiling plays; **Mickey Moniak** is in a prime spot against the struggling Matt Waldron (7.83 xERA), while **James Wood** leverages a leadoff position to maximize opportunities for stolen bases and runs\u2014the two categories most critical to our roster construction.\n\nThe bench decision process was tight, ultimately sidelining **Brice Turang** (46.38) in favor of deeper lineup utility. While **Brice Turang** carries elite stolen base potential, his matchup against a difficult southpaw in Tarik Skubal (2.71 xERA) effectively neutralized his score, pushing him below the threshold required to displace starters like **Jose Caballero** or **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, who are facing more favorable pitching conditions. We are exercising caution with **Dalton Rushing** (40.27) and **Seiya Suzuki** (50.54), as both face legitimate aces in Logan Webb and Cristopher S\u00e1nchez, respectively; while **Seiya Suzuki** is aided by favorable wind conditions today, both players are on \"start-only-if-necessary\" watch.\n\nInvestors should note that today\u2019s lineup remains fluid with most slots listed as \"Lineup Pending.\" Any late-arriving news shifting **Dalton Rushing** or **Luis Campusano** lower in the order could further compress their scoring projections. **Kyle Karros** (61.48) represents a sneaky value play\u2014his high score is heavily inflated by the 14% park factor and the massive 19% SP skill edge against Matt Waldron, making him a high-leverage start despite his usual spot in the bottom third of the lineup. Proceed with these projections until official lineups are confirmed.",
